<doc id="515597" wikidata="Q1339454" url="?curid=515597" title="La Grande-3 generating station">
<text>The La Grande-3 or LG-3 is a hydroelectric dam on the La Grande River in northern Quebec, part of Hydro-Québec&#x27;s James Bay Project. The station can generate 2,418 MW and was commissioned in 1982–1984. It generates electricity through the reservoir and dam system. The dam and reservoir both are named &quot;La Grande-3&quot;. The community of Sakami was founded for its construction.
